5:
He really drew every single one of
them... And they all look great.
12:
Oops... Sorry, Leon. Staying up all
night is tough at my age.
15:
Don't push yourself so hard, Gramps.
You've earned some rest.
19:
Oh, quit it. No matter how creaky my
joints get, an adventurer never gives
up when the treasure is right in front
of him!
26:
How long are you planning on
staying in Yamato?
29:
Huh? Well, uh... I thought I'd take it
easy here for a while yet.
33:
That so? Damn... These eyes of mine
must be getting old.
36:
All I see is a kid that can't wait to go
out on his next adventure.
41:
...You artists have an eye for reading
expressions, huh.
45:
By the way, they're planning to have
a lantern festival at a nearby river
tonight.
51:
...Geez, how could I say no after all
that?
60:
I see. So it's a ceremony for the
departed.
64:
Yeah. The people light lanterns to
help the dead find their way back
home.
70:
Yeah... That crazy old painter gave
me a chance to see them all again,
didn't he...
85: ...Heh. It's just like the old man said...
88: Looks like... I needed this after all.
106:
You've got it. Just place it in the river
and let it go...
119:
...Never mind. I can't put the words
together.
122: That's just how it is, Alk.
127:
I guess we both have our share of
regrets.
130:
If only I had fought harder, taken a
different path... said something in
advance...
139:
That said, nothing good comes from
spending your whole life caught up
in regret.
142:
How would their souls find peace
otherwise?
145: I wish I could be strong like you.
148:
But you are, Alk. Or did you give up
already?
151: I haven't... And I won't, either.
154:
Then you've got nothing to worry
about.
157:
Nobody knows what will happen if
you all continue down the road
you're on.
160:
I can't tell you where you need to go,
and I doubt you'd want that anyway.
162:
But when the heat comes down,
don't forget we've all got your back.
164:
So just relax and put your best foot
forward.
172:
We're ADVENTURERS! Reason be
damned, we'll overcome the
impossible and grab our dreams
with our own bare hands!
175:
Tell your enemies about us! They
don't stand a chance!
182:
Farewell, comrades. Watch over us,
all right?
186:
My new friends and I have many
adventures ahead of us.
193:
Good morning... Uh, wait, Leon? Why
aren't you wearing your yukata?
196:
Didn't need it anymore. My
vacation's over!
200:
Geez. Would it have killed you to
give us a little more warning?
204:
It's all right. We were also planning
on departing soon enough.
208: Well, then. Are we ready to go?
213:
I sure am. Time for another
heart-pounding adventure!
